# Context Recovery Bootstrap

Every Cursor chat must assume **zero chat history**. Recover durable project state from the repo before acting.

## Control store paths (manifest-driven)

Read `ordia.yaml` first. Let **`{controlRoot}`** = `control.root` from the manifest (greenfield default: `docs/control/`).

| Artifact | Path |
|---|---|
| Live state | `{controlRoot}/ORCHESTRATION_STATE.md` |
| Recovery runbook | `{controlRoot}/CONTROL_PLANE_RECOVERY_RUNBOOK.md` when present |
| Task execution protocol | `{controlRoot}/TASK_EXECUTION_PROTOCOL.md` when present |
| Task registry | `{controlRoot}/TASK_REGISTRY.yaml` |
| Agent registry | `{controlRoot}/AGENT_REGISTRY.yaml` |
| Task packets | `{controlRoot}/tasks/<Task ID>.md` |
| Decision log | `{controlRoot}/DECISION_LOG.md` |
| Evidence index | `{controlRoot}/EVIDENCE_INDEX.md` |
| Model tier profile | `{controlRoot}/MODEL_REGISTRY.yaml` (ORDIA-D022) |
| Runtime protocols | `{controlRoot}/protocols/` when present (`ORDIA-D007`); else `{controlRoot}/*_PROTOCOL.md` (profile legacy layout) |
| Handoff protocol | `{controlRoot}/RUNTIME_HANDOFF_PROTOCOL.md` when present |
| Project profile | `{controlRoot}/{projectProfile}` from manifest (`PROFILE.md` default) |
| Command overlay | `{controlRoot}/{commands.profileDoc}` when `commands:` is configured (`COMMANDS.md` default) |

Product specs remain under `docs/ordia/` when present. Root **`AGENTS.md`** is Ordia bootstrap only (not the domain profile).

## When to run bootstrap

Run on the **first change-capable turn** of a session, and whenever the user says continue, recover, resume, or provides an executor/control-plane report without context.

**Shortcut (ORDIA-D023):** `npm run ordia:prompt -- emit --intent recover` — emits header + recovery checklist; paste into chat or use as bootstrap guide.

## Mandatory read order

Read in this order (use Read tool or equivalent; do not skip):

1. `ordia.yaml` — resolve `{controlRoot}`, `{projectProfile}`, and `enforcement.productRoots`
2. `{controlRoot}/ORCHESTRATION_STATE.md` — **§0 Active Execution Control** first (include `session_mode` when present)
3. `{controlRoot}/{projectProfile}` — domain profile (agents, guardrails, tracks)
4. Root `AGENTS.md` when present — Ordia bootstrap pointers only
5. `{controlRoot}/CONTROL_PLANE_RECOVERY_RUNBOOK.md` when the file exists
6. `{controlRoot}/TASK_EXECUTION_PROTOCOL.md` when the file exists
7. `{controlRoot}/TASK_REGISTRY.yaml`
8. `{controlRoot}/AGENT_REGISTRY.yaml`
9. Selected runtime protocol (from header rule matrix; paths under `{controlRoot}`)
10. Active task packet at `{controlRoot}/tasks/<Active task ID>.md` when Active task ID is not `NONE`
11. `{controlRoot}/DECISION_LOG.md` — entries referenced by the task or state
12. `{controlRoot}/EVIDENCE_INDEX.md` — when task or state references evidence
13. `docs/ENGINEERING_STANDARDS.md` before product code changes when the file exists
14. `{controlRoot}/{commands.profileDoc}` before tests, builds, seeds, audits, or QA commands when configured
15. `{controlRoot}/RUNTIME_HANDOFF_PROTOCOL.md` when `handoff_from` is not `NONE`

If `handoff_from` is not `NONE`, reconcile handoff before resuming `IN_FLIGHT` work.

## Unified session recovery (`session_mode: UNIFIED`)

When §0 records `session_mode: UNIFIED` (RUNTIME-D005):

1. Read unified orchestration rules (`{controlRoot}/CURSOR_ORCHESTRATION_PROTOCOL.md` §5.1 or `{controlRoot}/protocols/CURSOR_ORCHESTRATION.md`) in addition to the selected protocol document.
2. Determine the current phase: **PLAN**, **EXECUTE**, **QA**, or **CLOSE** (from task packet, registry, and chat context — not from `active_protocol` alone).
3. Before any product-code edit under configured `enforcement.productRoots`, confirm the user has explicitly approved the implementation slice.
4. After QA `ACCEPT`, execute the RUNTIME-D006 closure checklist in `{controlRoot}/TASK_EXECUTION_PROTOCOL.md` before marking `VALIDATED`.

## Continue in-flight tasks

When `{controlRoot}/ORCHESTRATION_STATE.md` or `{controlRoot}/TASK_REGISTRY.yaml` `queues.in_flight` shows an active task:

1. Load its task packet; confirm objective, scope, locks, dependencies, waiting state, pending evidence.
2. Do **not** infer completion from chat; trust registry + packet + evidence only.
3. Resume at **next safe action** recorded in state/packet — do not restart from scratch unless the packet says so.
4. Respect `planned_write_paths`, `blocked_paths`, and active locks in the registry.

## Validation gate

Run `ordia validate --project` before implementation and after material state transitions. **Do not implement while validation reports errors.**

## Recovery verdict (report to user before acting)

Use exactly one:

- `RECOVERY_READY` — state coherent; next safe action known
- `RECOVERY_NEEDS_USER_CONFIRMATION` — missing Runtime, Protocol, or user decision
- `RECOVERY_BLOCKED` — lock conflict, registry/state mismatch, or failed validation

Report: recovered runtime/protocol, `session_mode` (if set), active task ID + status, UNIFIED phase (if applicable), locks, in-flight work, pending evidence, contradictions, next safe action.
